      "id": "spine_biology_l4_catecholamine_dopamine_signaling",
      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_neurotransmitters_and_receptors",
      "content": {
        "title": "Catecholamine and Dopamine Signaling",
        "definition": "Biosynthesis of dopamine, norepinephrine, and epinephrine from tyrosine with distinct receptor subtypes (D1–D5, α, β) mediating diverse autonomic and CNS effects.",
        "summary": "Catecholamines act through GPCRs. Dopamine pathways in basal ganglia underlie motor and reward circuitry."
      },
