      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_neurotransmitters_and_receptors",
      "content": {
        "title": "Cholinergic Signaling",
        "definition": "Acetylcholine-mediated neurotransmission at nicotinic receptors (ionotropic) in autonomic ganglia and NMJ and muscarinic receptors (GPCR) in parasympathetic effectors.",
        "summary": "ACh is synthesized from choline and acetyl-CoA. Acetylcholinesterase terminates signaling at synapses."
      },
