      "id": "spine_biology_l4_ligand_gated_vs_gpcr_receptors",
      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_neurotransmitters_and_receptors",
      "content": {
        "title": "Ligand-Gated Ion Channels vs Metabotropic Receptors",
        "definition": "Ionotropic receptors mediate fast synaptic potentials via direct ion channel opening; metabotropic GPCRs modulate ion channels through second messenger cascades.",
        "summary": "Nicotinic ACh and GABA-A are ionotropic. Muscarinic ACh and adrenergic receptors are metabotropic with slower, modulatory effects."
      },
