      "content": {
        "title": "Major Neurotransmitter Systems",
        "definition": "Principal neurotransmitters including glutamate (excitatory), GABA (inhibitory), acetylcholine, dopamine, and serotonin with distinct synthesis pathways and functional roles.",
        "summary": "Each neurotransmitter system has characteristic anatomical distribution and behavioral correlates. Balance between excitation and inhibition is essential for normal neural function."
